From: stopless-java-gc <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH 0039/N] java.desktop Gensrc.gmk: include X11 wrapper gen on bsd target

`make/modules/java.desktop/Gensrc.gmk` only includes
`GensrcX11Wrappers.gmk` when `OPENJDK_TARGET_OS` is `linux` or
`aix`. The wrapper generator runs `TOOL_WRAPPERGENERATOR` on the
pre-baked size tables `make/data/x11wrappergen/sizes-{32,64}.txt`
— no actual X11 headers required, so this works on any target
that has X11 layout matching the pre-baked sizes.

For `bsd` target, X11 follows the same layout as Linux (FreeBSD's
xorg-server uses the same Xlib ABI), so we can reuse `sizes-64.txt`.
Adding `bsd` to the gating predicate makes
`XEvent.java`, `XClientMessageEvent.java`, etc. get generated,
which unblocks 481 `cannot find symbol XEvent` errors in
`src/java.desktop/unix/classes/sun/awt/X11/*.java`.

Refs: docs/05_zgc_cheri_collision_report.md §6 (patch 0039)

--- a/make/modules/java.desktop/Gensrc.gmk
+++ b/make/modules/java.desktop/Gensrc.gmk
@@ -34,7 +34,7 @@ ifeq ($(call isTargetOs, windows), false)
   include gensrc/GensrcIcons.gmk
 endif

-ifeq ($(call isTargetOs, linux aix), true)
+ifeq ($(call isTargetOs, linux aix bsd), true)
   include gensrc/GensrcX11Wrappers.gmk
 endif

